<item>
            <title>[LU-18068] Test memcg for Lustre with CGroup V2</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18068</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The newer OS (i.e. rhel9.4) is using new CGroup V2 interface and abandoned the CGroup V1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The memcg testing in sanity/test_411 test cases are still using the old V1 interface.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It results in the. memcg testing on the newer system are skipped:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
        local cg_basedir=/sys/fs/cgroup/memory
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; # LU-9966
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; test -f &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;$cg_basedir/memory.kmem.limit_in_bytes&quot;&lt;/span&gt; ||
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; skip &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;no setup &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; cgroup&quot;&lt;/span&gt;  &amp;lt;= CGROUP V1&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This ticket is using to track the testing and performance benchmark with memcg on new CGroup V2 interface on newer version of the OS.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
